-- Create BlueBike table with matching data types (internal sql table)

CREATE TABLE BlueBike (
    ride_id NVARCHAR(100),
    rideable_type NVARCHAR(100),
    started_at DATETIME,
    ended_at DATETIME,
    start_station_name NVARCHAR(100),
    start_station_id NVARCHAR(100),
    end_station_name NVARCHAR(100),
    end_station_id NVARCHAR(100),
    start_lat FLOAT,
    start_lng FLOAT,
    end_lat FLOAT,
    end_lng FLOAT,
    member_casual NVARCHAR(100),
    is_bike_lost INT,
    is_return_to_dock INT,
    is_start_from_dock INT,
    distance FLOAT,
    duration FLOAT,
    speed_ms FLOAT,
    speed_kmh FLOAT,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE,
    is_not_return_to_dock INT,
    is_not_start_from_dock INT,
    duration_min FLOAT,
    duration_h FLOAT
);
GO

-- Insert data into BlueBike

INSERT INTO BlueBike (
    ride_id,
    rideable_type,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    start_station_name,
    start_station_id,
    end_station_name,
    end_station_id,
    start_lat,
    start_lng,
    end_lat,
    end_lng,
    member_casual,
    is_bike_lost,
    is_return_to_dock,
    is_start_from_dock,
    distance,
    duration,
    speed_ms,
    speed_kmh,
    start_date,
    end_date,
    is_not_return_to_dock,
    is_not_start_from_dock,
    duration_min,
    duration_h
)
SELECT
    ride_id,
    rideable_type,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    start_station_name,
    start_station_id,
    end_station_name,
    end_station_id,
    start_lat,
    start_lng,
    end_lat,
    end_lng,
    member_casual,
    is_bike_lost,
    is_return_to_dock,
    is_start_from_dock,
    distance,
    duration,
    speed_ms,
    speed_kmh,
    start_date,
    end_date,
    is_not_return_to_dock,
    is_not_start_from_dock,
    duration_min,
    duration_h
FROM 
    ExternalBluebike;
GO
